CatDescriptText: Wilbert Jones, mill worker, 1109 Liverpool Street, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 17, 1959, pg. A1 with question: "Do you believe that city patrolmen and firemen should be required to work more than 40 hours per week?" answer reads: "Not unless there is extra pay..."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Wilbert Jones wearing eyeglasses, hat, and striped shirt with dark sleeves and trim, standing on crutches in front of Jenkins Arcade, Liberty Avenue, Downtown
